Welcome to SecurePay
Welcome to SecurePay!
Hi {!Application__c.ContactFirstName__c},
Welcome to SecurePay! Your merchant account has been approved and you are almost ready to start accepting payments.
What do you need to do now?
In order to start accepting payments on your website, you or your web developer needs to update your website with the live SecurePay merchant account credentials. Once this has been done you can start processing real payments.
Transaction Merchant ID: {!Application__c.SecurePayTransactionMerchantID__c} Live transaction password: {!Application__c.SecurePayTransactionKeyPassword__c}
For more information on how to integrate, please refer to the Other API Integration Options which will provide you the technical details to integrate and test credentials for each of the API integration options available.
Your login details to the Merchant Portal
The Merchant Portal will be a handy tool once you are set up and start processing payments. You will be able to:
manage your transactions create reports search for transactions process credit card and bulk payments schedule future payments
You can login to the Merchant Portal using the below login details. It’s important to note the Merchant Portal is separate to your SecurePay online account and login details will differ.
Merchant ID: {!Application__c.SecurePayPortalMerchantID__c} User name: {!Application__c.SecurePayPortalUserId__c} Login password: {!Application__c.SecurePayPortalOneTimePassword__c}
The first time you login to your Merchant Portal you will be asked to change your password so it’s unique to you.
Terms and Conditions
We have attached a copy of the Online Payment Services Terms and Conditions for your reference.
Have a question?
Call our support team on 1300 786 756 or email us at support@securepay.com.au
Our support team is available Monday to Friday, 8am to 8pm Australian Eastern Standard Time (AEST). We are closed on public holidays and weekends.
Thank you for using SecurePay. We look forward to working with you.
All the best,
The SecurePay Team
NAB provides the merchant banking services, which includes the authorisation, processing and settling of the cardholder’s card transactions to the merchant. This email was sent by Australia Post.
